---
source: tests/mcp_server.rs
assertion_line: 30
expression: summary
---
- description: "Returns the processes inside a given cgroup. Takes a cgroup_path in normalized form (relative to /sys/fs/cgroup, no leading slash, empty string for the root cgroup) and returns each process with comm, cmdline, state, ppid, and rss_bytes. Use this to drill into a cgroup identified via cgroup-mcp's tools. The cgroup_path from any cgroup-mcp output can be passed here verbatim; both servers use the same identifier convention. Results are sorted descending by rss_bytes, with null values (kernel threads with no userspace memory map) last. cmdline args matching *key*=*, *token*=*, *password*=*, *secret*=* are redacted by default; set redact_args=false to receive them verbatim. The `skipped` field counts PIDs encountered in /proc that could not be fully read (transient process death, permission denied). Non-zero means the snapshot may be incomplete."
  input_schema:
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      cgroup_path:
        description: "Cgroup path to filter by, in normalized form: relative to\n`/sys/fs/cgroup`, no leading slash, empty string for the root\ncgroup. Example: `\"system.slice/nginx.service\"`. Take this value\nverbatim from any cgroup-mcp tool output that returns cgroup\npaths. Must not be absolute and must not contain `..` segments."
        type: string
      redact_args:
        default: ~
        description: "If true (the default), command-line arguments whose key matches\n`*key*=*`, `*token*=*`, `*password*=*`, `*secret*=*`\n(case-insensitive) are replaced with `key=REDACTED` in the\nreturned `cmdline`. Set to false to receive verbatim cmdlines at\nthe risk of leaking secrets that were passed as CLI args."
        type:
          - boolean
          - "null"
    required:
      - cgroup_path
    title: PidsInCgroupParams
    type: object
  name: pids_in_cgroup
  output_schema:
    $defs:
      ProcessEntry:
        properties:
          cgroup_path:
            description: "Normalized cgroup path. Same convention as cgroup-mcp: relative to\n`/sys/fs/cgroup`, no leading slash, empty string for the root."
            type: string
          cmdline:
            description: "Space-joined cmdline from `/proc/<pid>/cmdline`. Empty for kernel\nthreads. Subject to the redaction flag the tool was called with."
            type: string
          comm:
            description: "15-character kernel name from `/proc/<pid>/comm`."
            type: string
          pid:
            format: uint32
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          ppid:
            format: uint32
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          rss_bytes:
            description: "Resident set size in bytes. Null for kernel threads, which have\nno userspace memory map."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type:
              - integer
              - "null"
          state:
            description: "Single-character state code from `/proc/<pid>/status`:\n`R`unning, `S`leeping, `D`isk-wait, `Z`ombie, `T`raced/stopped,\n`I`dle (kernel threads). Returned as a string for JSON portability."
            type: string
        required:
          - pid
          - comm
          - cmdline
          - state
          - ppid
          - cgroup_path
        type: object
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      cgroup_path:
        description: Echoes the queried cgroup_path.
        type: string
      results:
        description: "Processes in the cgroup, sorted descending by `rss_bytes` (null\nvalues last)."
        items:
          $ref: "#/$defs/ProcessEntry"
        type: array
      skipped:
        description: "Count of PIDs encountered in `/proc` that could not be fully read\n(transient process death, permission denied, etc.). Non-zero\nmeans the snapshot may be incomplete."
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
    required:
      - cgroup_path
      - results
      - skipped
    title: PidsInCgroupResponse
    type: object
- description: "Returns the full per-PID drill-down bundle for one process. Includes the same identifier fields as pids_in_cgroup (pid, comm, cmdline, state, ppid, rss_bytes, cgroup_path) plus uid, num_threads, fd_count, a smaps_rollup memory breakdown (Rss/Pss/Shared/Private/Anon/Swap), and IO counters. Use this after identifying a PID of interest via pids_in_cgroup or top_processes. The `memory.pss_bytes` field is the fairest single number for 'this process's memory cost' when pages are shared with other processes (browser tabs, JVM workers, etc.). Permission-gated fields are nullable when the kernel rejects the read: `fd_count` and `io` typically require ptrace capability or matching uid; `memory` is null for kernel threads. Cmdline args matching *key=*, *token=*, *password=*, *secret=* are redacted by default; pass `redact_args=false` to receive them verbatim. Errors if the PID does not exist."
  input_schema:
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      pid:
        description: "PID of the process to drill into. Must currently exist in\n`/proc/<pid>/`."
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
      redact_args:
        default: ~
        description: "If true (the default), command-line arguments whose key matches\n`*key*=*`, `*token*=*`, `*password*=*`, `*secret*=*`\n(case-insensitive) are replaced with `key=REDACTED`."
        type:
          - boolean
          - "null"
    required:
      - pid
    title: ProcessInfoParams
    type: object
  name: process_info
  output_schema:
    $defs:
      IoCounters:
        description: "IO counters from `/proc/<pid>/io`. Cumulative since process start.\nReading this file typically requires ptrace capability or matching\nuid; non-root callers commonly hit EACCES."
        properties:
          read_bytes:
            description: "Bytes read from disk (after the page cache). Matches kernel\n`read_bytes`."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          read_syscalls:
            description: "Number of read syscalls. Matches kernel `syscr`."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          write_bytes:
            description: "Bytes written to disk. Matches kernel `write_bytes`."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          write_syscalls:
            description: "Number of write syscalls. Matches kernel `syscw`."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
        required:
          - read_bytes
          - write_bytes
          - read_syscalls
          - write_syscalls
        type: object
      MemoryBreakdown:
        description: "Memory breakdown from `/proc/<pid>/smaps_rollup`. All values in bytes."
        properties:
          anon_bytes:
            description: "Anonymous (non-file-backed) memory: heap, stacks, malloc'd regions."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          private_bytes:
            description: "`Private_Clean + Private_Dirty`: pages mapped only by this process."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          pss_bytes:
            description: "Proportional set size: each shared page is counted in proportion to\nthe number of processes mapping it. The fairest single number for\n\"this process's memory cost\" when pages are shared across processes\n(browser tabs, JVM workers, etc.)."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          rss_bytes:
            description: "Resident set size: physical memory currently mapped to this process."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          shared_bytes:
            description: "`Shared_Clean + Shared_Dirty`: pages mapped by multiple processes."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          swap_bytes:
            description: Swapped-out pages.
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
        required:
          - rss_bytes
          - pss_bytes
          - shared_bytes
          - private_bytes
          - anon_bytes
          - swap_bytes
        type: object
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      cgroup_path:
        description: "Normalized cgroup path. Same convention as cgroup-mcp: relative to\n`/sys/fs/cgroup`, no leading slash, empty string for the root."
        type: string
      cmdline:
        description: "Space-joined cmdline from `/proc/<pid>/cmdline`. Empty for kernel\nthreads. Subject to the redaction flag the tool was called with."
        type: string
      comm:
        description: "15-character kernel name from `/proc/<pid>/comm`."
        type: string
      fd_count:
        description: "Count of entries in `/proc/<pid>/fd/`. Null if the directory was\nunreadable due to permissions (common for non-root callers)."
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type:
          - integer
          - "null"
      io:
        anyOf:
          - $ref: "#/$defs/IoCounters"
          - type: "null"
        description: "Cumulative IO counters from `/proc/<pid>/io`. Null when the file\nis unreadable (EACCES is very common as non-root)."
      memory:
        anyOf:
          - $ref: "#/$defs/MemoryBreakdown"
          - type: "null"
        description: "Memory breakdown from `/proc/<pid>/smaps_rollup`. Null for kernel\nthreads (no userspace memory map) or when EACCES."
      num_threads:
        description: Number of threads in the process group.
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
      pid:
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
      ppid:
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
      rss_bytes:
        description: "Resident set size in bytes. Null for kernel threads, which have\nno userspace memory map."
        format: uint64
        minimum: 0
        type:
          - integer
          - "null"
      state:
        description: "Single-character state code from `/proc/<pid>/status`:\n`R`unning, `S`leeping, `D`isk-wait, `Z`ombie, `T`raced/stopped,\n`I`dle (kernel threads). Returned as a string for JSON portability."
        type: string
      uid:
        description: Real uid that owns the process.
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
    required:
      - pid
      - comm
      - cmdline
      - state
      - ppid
      - cgroup_path
      - uid
      - num_threads
    title: ProcessInfoResponse
    type: object
- description: "Returns the top N processes ranked by resident memory (rss_bytes), descending. Use this to answer 'what's using the most memory on this box.' Pass `cgroup_prefix` to scope the search to a cgroup subtree. The match is path-aware: `system.slice` matches `system.slice` itself and any descendant (e.g. `system.slice/nginx.service`), but NOT siblings like `system.slice2`. Take cgroup paths verbatim from any cgroup-mcp tool output. Results are returned with the same shape as `pids_in_cgroup`: pid, comm, cmdline (redacted by default; pass `redact_args=false` for verbatim), state, ppid, rss_bytes, and cgroup_path. Kernel threads (null rss_bytes) sort last. Default n is 10. CPU-based ranking is planned but not yet implemented; current sort is memory only."
  input_schema:
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      cgroup_prefix:
        default: ~
        description: "If supplied, only consider processes whose cgroup path equals\nthis prefix or is a descendant of it. Path-aware matching:\n`system.slice` matches `system.slice` itself and any path\nstarting with `system.slice/`, but never `system.slice2/...`.\nEmpty string and omitted both mean \"consider all processes.\"\nMust not be absolute or contain `..` segments."
        type:
          - string
          - "null"
      n:
        default: ~
        description: Maximum number of processes to return. Defaults to 10.
        format: uint
        minimum: 0
        type:
          - integer
          - "null"
      redact_args:
        default: ~
        description: "If true (the default), command-line arguments whose key matches\n`*key*=*`, `*token*=*`, `*password*=*`, `*secret*=*`\n(case-insensitive) are replaced with `key=REDACTED`."
        type:
          - boolean
          - "null"
    title: TopProcessesParams
    type: object
  name: top_processes
  output_schema:
    $defs:
      ProcessEntry:
        properties:
          cgroup_path:
            description: "Normalized cgroup path. Same convention as cgroup-mcp: relative to\n`/sys/fs/cgroup`, no leading slash, empty string for the root."
            type: string
          cmdline:
            description: "Space-joined cmdline from `/proc/<pid>/cmdline`. Empty for kernel\nthreads. Subject to the redaction flag the tool was called with."
            type: string
          comm:
            description: "15-character kernel name from `/proc/<pid>/comm`."
            type: string
          pid:
            format: uint32
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          ppid:
            format: uint32
            minimum: 0
            type: integer
          rss_bytes:
            description: "Resident set size in bytes. Null for kernel threads, which have\nno userspace memory map."
            format: uint64
            minimum: 0
            type:
              - integer
              - "null"
          state:
            description: "Single-character state code from `/proc/<pid>/status`:\n`R`unning, `S`leeping, `D`isk-wait, `Z`ombie, `T`raced/stopped,\n`I`dle (kernel threads). Returned as a string for JSON portability."
            type: string
        required:
          - pid
          - comm
          - cmdline
          - state
          - ppid
          - cgroup_path
        type: object
    $schema: "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema"
    properties:
      cgroup_prefix:
        description: Echoes the cgroup_prefix filter (or null if not provided).
        type:
          - string
          - "null"
      results:
        description: "Top processes, sorted descending by `rss_bytes`, with null values\n(kernel threads) at the end."
        items:
          $ref: "#/$defs/ProcessEntry"
        type: array
      skipped:
        description: "Count of PIDs encountered in `/proc` that could not be fully read\n(transient process death, permission denied, etc.). Non-zero\nmeans the snapshot may be incomplete."
        format: uint32
        minimum: 0
        type: integer
    required:
      - results
      - skipped
    title: TopProcessesResponse
    type: object
